      enhance the inhibitory effect of all 10(7) CFU/ml Lactobacillus strains
      against KPC001. Three Lactobacillus strains (LYC1154, LYC1322, and
      LYC1511) that could be persistently detected in the stool were tested for
      their ability to reduce the amount of KPC001 in the feces individually or
      in combination. A significantly better effect in reducing the amount of
      KPC001 was observed for the combination of three different Lactobacillus
      species than for each of them alone. Furthermore, their inhibitory effect
