      hypermucoviscosity phenotype was confirmed by string test. Whole-genome
      sequencing (WGS) analysis revealed the presence of an ST13 KPC70-producing
      K. pneumoniae, a KPC-3 variant, differing in two amino-acid substitutions
      (D179Y and T263A). The D179Y mutation in the KPC Ω-loop region is the most
      common amino-acid substitution in KPC-2 and KPC-3, further leading to CZA
