AB  - Klebsiella pneumoniae is an important pathogen that causes pneumonia and
      bloodstream infections, especially in neonates and intensive care
      patients. The carbapenems remain an important therapeutic option for
      clinicians, particularly against cephalosporin-resistant Gram-negative
