AB  - The increased prevalence of carbapenemase-producing Enterobacteriaceae
      (CPE) has made essential the design of quicker tests for CPE detection. In
      the present study, a simple and rapid assay was developed based on
      measurement of the hydrolytic activity of imipenem at a final
      concentration of 65 µg/mL (100 µM) through ultraviolet-visible (UV-Vis)
      spectrophotometry. All measurements were conducted at 297 nm. A total of
      83 carbapenem-non-susceptible CPE, consisting of Klebsiella pneumoniae
      clinical isolates and genotypically characterised as KPC-, VIM-, NDM- or
