      CPE from non-CPE isolates even in 45 min (P < 0.0001). Moreover, the
      presence of phenylboronic acid (PBA) or ethylene diamine tetra-acetic acid
      (EDTA) in the reaction mixture was able to inhibit the hydrolytic capacity
      of KPC- or metallo-β-lactamase (MBL)-producers, respectively, while the
      hydrolytic activity of OXA-48-producing strains was not affected by the
      presence of these inhibitors (P < 0.001). The newly developed assay
      presented 100% sensitivity and specificity to detect and differentiate
      KPC-, MBL- and OXA-48-producers compared with genotypic characterisation.
