AB  - Klebsiella pneumoniae carbapenemase (KPC)-producing Enterobacteriaceae
      have been isolated from human patients in many countries across the globe
      but rarely in Saudi Arabia. Here we provide the genomic characterization
      of the first KPC-producing K. pneumoniae isolated from the urine of a
      patient in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, who had a recent travel history to Egypt
      involving a medical procedure. Presence of KPC-encoding gene initially
      detected with the Xpert Carba-R assay was confirmed by traditional PCR.
