      important challenge in healthcare settings. Currently,
      carbapenem-resistant Klebsiella pneumoniae (CRKP) are the species of CRE
      most commonly encountered in hospitals. CRKP is resistant to almost all
      available antimicrobial agents, and infections with CRKP have been
      associated with high rates of morbidity and mortality, particularly among
      persons with prolonged hospitalization exposed to invasive devices. We
      report nine patients hospitalized in an intensive care unit (ICU) with
