      inoculation, treatment for 7 days started in seven groups of ≥10 rabbits,
      including a control group, a colistin group, and one group for each
      meropenem product (i.e. the innovator and four generics), in combination
      with colistin. In vitro, meropenem + colistin was bactericidal with no
      viable bacteria after 6 h, and this effect was similar with all meropenem
      products. In the osteomyelitis model, there was no significant difference
      between meropenem generics and the innovator when combined with colistin.
      Colistin-resistant strains were detected after treatment with colistin +
      meropenem innovator (n = 3) and generics (n = 3). The efficacy of four
