      colonization of sink P-traps by carbapenemase-producing Klebsiella
      pneumoniae (CPKP), causing CPKP dispersal into the patient care
      environment. This study aimed to determine the effect of LW on biofilm
      formation and CPKP colonization in a P-Trap model (PTM). PTMs containing
      polymicrobial biofilms grown in autoclaved municipal tap water (ATW)
      supplemented with 5% dextrose in water (D5W), nutritional shake (Shake),
