      Kp14U04 harboured a multiple stress resistance protein, efflux systems and
      regulators, heavy metal resistance and virulence genes, plasmids,
      prophage-related sequences and genomic islands. These features revealed
      the high potential of this isolate to resist antimicrobial therapy,
      survive in adverse environments, cause infections and overcome host
      defence mechanisms.
