AB  - New Delhi metallo-β-lactamase (NDM) had been reported to be the
      predominant carbapenemase among Escherichia coli in Taiwan. However,
      studies focusing on the clonal background and epidemiology of plasmids
      carrying NDM genes were limited. Between 2016 and 2018, all clinical E.
      coli and Klebsiella pneumoniae isolates that were non-susceptible to
      ertapenem, meropenem, and imipenem were tested for carbapenemase-encoding
      genes (CEGs) and antimicrobial susceptibilities. Molecular typing was
      performed on all carbapenemase-producing isolates. Whole genome sequencing
