AB  - We report the case of successful use of cefiderocol (FDC) in a
      Carbapenemase Producing K. pneumoniae (CPKP) post-surgical meningitis in a
      44-year-old man treated with antimicrobial therapy and external
      ventricular drainage (EVD). The patient was known for being colonised by
      CPKP; for this reason, therapy with ceftazidime/avibactam (CZA) plus
      fosfomycin and linezolid was started. After an initial response a CZA
