AB  - Antimicrobial peptides may be alternatives to traditional antibiotics with
      reduced bacterial resistance. The antimicrobial peptide GL13K was derived
      from the salivary protein BPIFA2. This study determined the relative
      activity of the L-and D-enantiomers of GL13K to wild-type and
      drug-resistant strains of three gram-negative species and against
