      and Klebsiella spp. (38.3%) were the dominant species. Whole-genome
      sequencing was performed on 169 representative isolates with a combination
      of short and long reads using Illumina and Nanopore technology. Two
      distinct lineages of bla(KPC-2)-positive Klebsiella pneumoniae (ST11 and
      ST258) were identified with ST11 carrying yersiniabactin gene ybt-9 on
