      with class B carbapenemases, P. aeruginosa carrying VIM carbapenemase and
      A. baumannii strains showed no changes on IMI MIC50 or MIC90 after adding
      REL. Among P. aeruginosa strains without carbapenemase the MIC for IMI/REL
      was reduced between 1 to 5 dilutions. CONCLUSIONS: IMI/REL showed high
      activity against the strains that carry Klebsiella pneumoniae
