AB  - OBJECTIVE: In total, 97 carbapenem-resistant Enterobacteriaceae (CRE) were
      collected from 17 hospitals located in Nanjing, Southeast China, and
      analyzed for epidemiological characteristics. METHODS: Antimicrobial
      susceptibility was determined; followed by determination of the prevalence
      of resistance determinants, including extended-spectrum β-lactamase
      (ESBLs), plasmid-mediated AmpC enzyme (pAmpCs), plasmid-mediated quinolone
      resistance genes (PMQRs), fosfomycin resistance gene and exogenously
      acquired 16S rRNA methyltransferase (16S-RMTase) using PCR and DNA
      sequencing. The sequence types (STs) of CRE were determined by multi-locus
      sequence typing (MLST). The plasmid profiles were detected by PCR-based
