      for aztreonam/avibactam, minocycline, ceftazidime/avibactam, tigecycline,
      and colistin. KPC-2 (79.4%) and NDM (19.6%) were the main carbapenemases,
      CTX-M (76.3%) and SHV (60.8%) were the predominant ESBLs. In addition,
      oqxAB (70.1%) and qnr (63.9%) were the major PMQRs; rmtB (47.4%) was the
