AB  - QPX7728 is an ultrabroad-spectrum boronic acid beta-lactamase inhibitor,
      with potent inhibition of key serine and metallo-beta-lactamases being
      observed in biochemical assays. Microbiological studies using
      characterized strains were used to provide a comprehensive
      characterization of the spectrum of beta-lactamase inhibition by QPX7728.
      The MICs of multiple antibiotics administered intravenously only
      (ceftazidime, piperacillin, cefepime, ceftolozane, and meropenem) and
      orally bioavailable antibiotics (ceftibuten, cefpodoxime, tebipenem) alone
      and in combination with QPX7728 (4 μg/ml), as well as comparator agents,
      were determined against panels of laboratory strains of Pseudomonas
      aeruginosa and Klebsiella pneumoniae expressing over 55 diverse serine and
      metallo-beta-lactamases. QPX7728 significantly enhanced the potency of
      antibiotics against strains expressing class A extended-spectrum
      beta-lactamases (CTX-M, SHV, TEM, VEB, PER) and carbapenemases (KPC, SME,
      NMC-A, BKC-1), consistent with the beta-lactamase inhibition demonstrated
      in biochemical assays. It also inhibited both plasmidic (CMY, FOX, MIR,
      DHA) and chromosomally encoded (P99, PDC, ADC) class C beta-lactamases and
      class D enzymes, including carbapenemases, such as OXA-48 from
      Enterobacteriaceae and OXA enzymes from Acinetobacter baumannii
