      the fungal analysis, Candida spp., Cryptococcus spp., Rhodotorula
      mucilaginosa, R. glutinis, and Trichosporon coremiiforme were identified.
      All the Trichosporon coremiiforme strains were resistant to amphotericin
      B, as well as all the Rhodotorula mucilaginosa exhibited resistance to
      fluconazole. Related to the biofilm production, among the 8 CoPS, 27
      enterobacteria, and 10 yeasts isolates, 3, 16, and 7 strains were biofilm
      producers, respectively. Thus, the presence of these microorganisms in
      birds of prey is worrisome, highlighting its possible influence in the
      spread of infections in urban centers.
